## LAN (Local Area Network)
- A Local Area Network connects devices in a small area (home, school, office)
- Devices can share files and internet

## Star Topology
- All devices connect to a central device (switch or hub)

Advantages:
- Reliable
- Easy to add devices
- One device failing does not affect others

Disadvantages:
- More expensive
- If central device fails, network goes down

## Bus Topology
- All devices share one main cable (backbone)

Advantages:
- Cheap
- Easy to set up

Disadvantages:
- Slower with more traffic
- Hard to troubleshoot
- If cable breaks, entire network fails

## Ring Topology
- Devices are connected in a loop

Advantages:
- Simple structure

Disadvantages:
- If one device fails, everything stops
- Slower data transfer

## Switch
- Connects devices in a network
- Sends data only to the correct device

## Router
- Connects different networks
- Sends data between networks

