# DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol)

DHCP automatically assigns IP addresses to devices on a network.

## DHCP Process (DORA)

## Discover
The device asks:
"Is there a DHCP server?"

## Offer
The server responds with an available IP address.

## Request
The device asks to use that IP address.

## Acknowledge (ACK)
The server confirms and allows the device to use the IP for a limited time (lease).

## Key Points
- IP addresses are temporary (leased)
- No manual setup needed
- Common in home and business networks

